description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking to recruit a (Bank) Assistant Cook to join our Catering Team, to cover annual leave, sickness and other absences on a casual basis. The rate of pay will be £8.90 per hour. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful applicant will have &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NVQ level 2 in Professional Cookery &amp; Food &amp; Beverage Service – or equivalent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Two years experience in a cook or assistant cook position&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience of cooking fresh produce&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Confident preparing and cooking a full range of nutritional meals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Preparing special dietary meals&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stock storage and rotation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Shifts are variable over 7 days covering the hours of 7.45am – 6pm, including weekends and bank holidays.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information and details on how to apply please see attachments&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;or contact Ruth Garrett on 0151 529 8389 or email &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;ruth.garrett@aintree.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
